[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpc_b0v7j_[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzz -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer-run test of the mongoose JSON parser [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`mg_json_get` in `src/json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered an AddressSanitizer-detected stack-buffer-overflow. The overflow occurs [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhen writing one byte past the end of a local array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`nesting`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m within [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`. The crash is reproducible under the fuzz harness and indicates [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mimproper bounds checking in the JSON parsing routine.[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Issue type  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  The failure is reported as a “stack-buffer-overflow” by AddressSanitizer. This [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindicates a write outside the bounds of a stack-allocated buffer.[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Observations  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The fuzzer [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/out/[0m[95mfuzz[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m ran under libFuzzer with an interactive mode dataset [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m and [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m runs.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • A single test input [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m triggered the overflow.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The crash stack trace:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. `mg_json_get` at `src/json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m`  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Called by `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `test/fuzz.[0m[1;92mc:81:3[0m[39m`  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. Then into libFuzzer internals [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`Fuzzer::ExecuteCallback`, `RunOneTest`, [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`FuzzerDriver`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m. Finally `main` from `FuzzerMain.cpp`.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Address [0m[1;36m0x7f67[0m[39m…f83e is in the stack frame of `mg_json_get`; the buffer named [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` is allocated there.  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • The overflow happens at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, whereas `nesting` spans offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdemonstrating a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte overwrite beyond the buffer’s right boundary.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Shadow memory notation shows an “f1” redzone just before the overflow point, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming stack redzone violation.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Vulnerability implications  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  A stack-buffer-overflow can corrupt adjacent stack data, potentially leading to [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontrol-flow hijacking, information leakage or denial of service. In a library [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext, this may impact any application embedding the mongoose JSON parser.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Relevant code areas for investigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. **src/json.c, function `mg_json_get`**  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Review the declaration and size of the `nesting` array.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Examine all loops or index calculations that write to this array.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Verify any depth‐tracking or recursion logic that increments the nesting [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mindex.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. **test/fuzz.c, function `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`**  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Understand how inputs are fed to `mg_json_get` and whether any pre‐ or [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpost‐processing affects array bounds.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. **Boundary constants or macros**  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Identify any constants controlling maximum JSON nesting depth.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     – Check for mismatches between assumed limits and actual buffer size.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Areas outside the direct crash location  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Higher-level JSON parsing entry points [0m[1;39m([0m[39mif any[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that dispatch to `mg_json_get`.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  • Any custom error‐handling or recovery paths that may bypass expected checks.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo root‐cause analysis or mitigation strategies are provided here. This report [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfocuses solely on capturing the symptoms, call chain, and code regions that should [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe reviewed to gain a complete understanding of the overflow.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a stack-buffer-overflow in mongoose’s JSON parser [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`mg_json_get` in `src/json.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. When fed certain inputs by the libFuzzer harness, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAddressSanitizer reports a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write just past the end of the local array [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting`, at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m of `json.c`.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA patch attempt was made to tighten the nesting-depth check in two places: changing[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto  [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor both object [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and array [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m entry cases.  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter re-running the fuzzer, the exact same overflow is still triggered at the same[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation, so the patch did not prevent the out-of-bounds write.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The libFuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m drives `mg_json_get` with [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39marbitrary data.  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer aborts on a stack-buffer-overflow: writing [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte at offset [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m62[0m[39m into the local array `nesting`, whose valid range is [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs at `src/json.[0m[1;92mc:186:28[0m[39m` inside `mg_json_get`, indicting a [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmissing or insufficient bounds check before indexing `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key observations from the failure log  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is reproducible: every run hits the same write beyond `nesting`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `nesting` is allocated on the stack; its size is tied to [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The sanitizer shadow bytes show a redzone immediately after `nesting`, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfirming a stack overflow.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`, two conditionals guarding entry into a deeper nesting level [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwere modified:  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[33m...[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     @@ [0m[1;36m-173[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m173[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m @@[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[33m...[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This is intended to prevent `depth` from ever reaching the array limit, by [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrefusing to descend when `depth == MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result after patch  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer log still reports a stack-buffer-overflow in `mg_json_get` at the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msame line and offset.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The bounds check changes did not intercept the problematic code path, so the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow persists unchanged.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for further investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The full definition and intended size of `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclaration of `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All code paths in `mg_json_get` that write to or read from `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, not [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39monly the branches for `[0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[39m` and `[0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m` but also any post-loop or error-handling [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer runs `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`, which calls `mg_json_get` in [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`src/mongoose/src/json.c`.[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer reports:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte write out of bounds on a stack variable `nesting`.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow occurs at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m in `json.c`.[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The array `nesting` spans offsets [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m in the stack frame, but the write is[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Stack trace excerpt:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m mg_json_get [0m[35m/src/mongoose/src/[0m[95mjson.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m186:28[0m[39m  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    #[0m[1;36m1[0m[39m LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput [0m[35m/src/mongoose/test/[0m[95mfuzz.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m81:3[0m[39m  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    …  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The report highlights that the local buffer `nesting` is too small for certain [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputs exercised by the fuzzer.[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- In `src/json.c`, the declaration[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  was changed to[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The intention was to allocate a larger buffer for `nesting`.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- No other changes were made to the function logic or bounds checking.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Patch[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The fuzzer was rerun for [0m[1;36m100[0m[39m iterations on the same test case.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- AddressSanitizer again reports a stack-buffer-overflow at the same address, same [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcode line [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, same offset [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The log structure, stack trace, and shadow bytes analysis are effectively [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical to the initial report.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- The variable `nesting` is still shown occupying [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, implying [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` did not increase the buffer size beyond [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch did not take effect[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Further Investigation[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo understand and resolve this overflow comprehensively, the following parts of the[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcodebase warrant a closer look:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Definitions of Depth Constants**  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verify the values of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` in header [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfiles.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirm which constant is actually in scope within `json.c` and whether the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplacement changed the array size.[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **mg_json_get Implementation**  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Examine the loop or logic that increments `depth` or writes into `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Identify all code paths that push or pop nesting levels and whether any bounds[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks exist.[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **JSON Input Handling**  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Review how `mg_json_get` processes nested JSON structures, especially deeply [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnested or malformed inputs.  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Determine the maximum theoretical nesting depth `mg_json_get` can reach and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether any existing limits are enforced.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Fuzzer Harness Parameters**  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Although not the root cause, review how the harness constructs inputs and [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhether it exercises extreme nesting patterns.  [0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Note if any corpus items or fuzzer flags bypass internal limits of the parser.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mBy examining these areas, one can get a holistic view of why `nesting` overflows [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand what measures [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., correct buffer sizing, explicit depth checks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are required[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto prevent out-of-bounds writes.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a one-byte stack-buffer-overflow detected by AddressSanitizer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39min the function `mg_json_get` [0m[1;39m([0m[39msrc/mongoose/src/json.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing certain [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzer inputs. The overflow occurs on a local array named `nesting`, which is [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdeclared with a size based on `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempt increased `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` from [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m in `json.h`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated the local buffer declaration from `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` to [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, and strengthened the depth-check conditions in [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get`. After applying the patch, the same stack-buffer-overflow is still [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered at the same code location and with the same offset, indicating the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow persists.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer report during a libFuzzer run on `fuzz`:  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Location: `mg_json_get` in `src/mongoose/src/json.c` at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Symptom: a write of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m to the stack at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m in the frame’s [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting` array.  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Stack frame:  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       - The local array `unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` occupies bytes [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m62[0m[39m, so writing at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m overruns its bounds.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * Fuzzer stack trace: shows `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` calling into [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`mg_json_get` with malformed or deeply nested JSON data that exercises the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * No other buffers or heap regions were implicated—in particular, the overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis on the function’s stack.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Key Observations in the Initial Log  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `nesting` buffer is too small for the nesting level encountered in the input. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is consistently reproducible with the given testcase.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The check for maximum depth uses a condition `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` but the actual allocated array is only `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize, introducing a mismatch.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.h`:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m128[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[33m...[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[33m...[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     + if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intention was to unify the buffer size and the runtime checks to prevent [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites past the end of `nesting`.[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Result After Applying the Patch  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer still reports the same stack-buffer-overflow at the same [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`json.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and offset [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m62[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The local array bounds have changed to [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m, but the overflow still occurs at [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor near the old boundary, indicating that either:  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The code path is writing beyond the new limit in runtime, or  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     * The mismatch between namespace constants [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` vs [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m still leads to an incorrect declaration or check.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The declaration and usage of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` vs `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboth header and implementation—ensure consistency.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The logic that governs `depth` increments and writes into `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mparticularly in loops that parse `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, and `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The index variables [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`i`, `depth`, `ed`, `ci`, `ei`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and how they relate to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe size of `path[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` and `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential off-by-one conditions in loop bounds or path-parsing branches that [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmight allow `depth` to equal or exceed the allocated buffer length before the check[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfires.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other stack-allocated buffers in `mg_json_get` that could be receiving [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrites under certain input shapes.[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:          i += [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.h:[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m12[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m9[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m10[0m[39m:#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m11[0m[39m:#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m:#endif[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m136[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m:  unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m131[0m[39m:  int i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current offset in `s`[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m132[0m[39m:  int j = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;             [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Offset in `s` we're looking for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mreturn value[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m133[0m[39m:  int depth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;         [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current depth [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnesting level[0m[1;39m)[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m134[0m[39m:  int ed = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Expected depth[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m135[0m[39m:  int pos = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m;           [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current position in `path`[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m136[0m[39m:  int ci = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Current and expected index in array[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:167[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m172[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m167[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m168[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'.'[0m[39m && ci == ei[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m169[0m[39m:            [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m If we start the object, reset array indices[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m170[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m171[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m172[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msrc/json.[0m[1;92mc:175[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m186[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m175[0m[39m:        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m176[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m177[0m[39m:          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m && ei == ci[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m178[0m[39m:            ed++, pos++, ci = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m179[0m[39m:            for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mei = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m[39m && path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[32m'\0'[0m[39m; pos++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m180[0m[39m:              ei *= [0m[1;36m10[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m181[0m[39m:              ei += path[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m - [0m[32m'0'[0m[39m;[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m182[0m[39m:            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m183[0m[39m:            if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mpath[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mpos[0m[1;39m][0m[39m != [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m pos++;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m184[0m[39m:          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m185[0m[39m:          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m186[0m[39m:          break;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Unify the compile‐time and runtime depth limits by eliminating the mismatched [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`:[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/json.h`, remove [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor alias[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m the separate `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` macro so [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat only one constant—`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`—governs both the size of the nesting [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer and all depth checks.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Option A [0m[1;39m([0m[39malias[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Remove or comment out the old MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH block:[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m#endif[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m After the MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING definition, add:[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        #define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Option B [0m[1;39m([0m[39mremove[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```c[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Delete the MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH macro entirely.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Retain only MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING, which defaults to [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor can be [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincreased[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        ```[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Ensure `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` is set to the maximum desired nesting [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m by [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdefault, or larger if needed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. If fuzz inputs require more headroom, bump this [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconstant—but do so in one place only.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. In `src/json.c`:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Change the nesting buffer declaration to use the unified macro:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Old:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m   unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m New:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m now same as [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Strengthen the depth‐overflow checks in **both** the `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` branches. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReplace all occurrences of:[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      with[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m([0m[39mUsing `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` here is equivalent to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` after [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munification.[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Verify that:[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;39m][0m[39m` is allocated with size `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` bytes, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatching the guard `depth < MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` before any write.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other local arrays use the old `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All paths that increment `depth` are preceded by the `>=` check.[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Rebuild and rerun the AddressSanitizer‐enabled fuzz target to confirm:[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack‐buffer‐overflow no longer triggers at line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m.[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legitimate JSON paths up to the new depth limit are still parsed correctly.[0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error code `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` is returned on inputs exceeding the configured [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnesting.[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mJustification:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- By aliasing or removing `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`, we eliminate the historic mismatch [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[1;36m30[0m[39m vs. [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m/[0m[1;36m128[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that allowed `depth` to exceed the buffer size.  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Converting the boundary check to `>=` prevents the off‐by‐one write at `depth == [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mMAX`.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Preserving a single macro for both compile‐time and runtime constraints maintains[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbackward compatibility [0m[1;39m([0m[39monly one macro to tune[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and keeps existing JSON‐path [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msemantics unchanged.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- This approach does not alter any harness or fuzzing logic, does not touch [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal dependencies, and leaves error‐return conventions intact.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Potential side effect: increasing the default nesting limit increases stack usage[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mby `N` bytes. However, with `N` on the order of [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m128[0m[39m, this remains minimal and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39macceptable for embedded/fuzzer environments.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Tests and consumption of `mg_json_get` will continue to operate as before; deeply[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnested inputs above the new limit will now deterministically fail with [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` rather than overflow.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo additional code retrieval is necessary, as the patch affects only `json.h` and [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`json.c`.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand increase the maximum nesting limits [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` raised from [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m to [0m   [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks from `depth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` to `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`. After [0m [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlocation, indicating the issue remains.[0m                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. mg_json_get [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjson.[0m[1;92mc:186[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.h`:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Removed `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` default of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m and `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` default [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mof [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Introduced `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` defaulted to [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m if not defined.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Defined `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` as an alias to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `src/json.c`:  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • At the branches handling `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m` and `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m` characters, changed the guard from  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       to  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;`  [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - These changes intended to raise the allowed nesting limit and ensure that once[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe configured limit is reached the function returns a “too deep” error before [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmodifying the stack-based `nesting` buffer.[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Post-Patch Fuzzing Result  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The same AddressSanitizer error recurred at `mg_json_get` line [0m[1;36m186[0m[39m with an [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical stack-buffer-overflow report on `nesting`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer size and overflow offset remained the same [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwrite at offset [0m[1;36m62[0m[39m of a[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m-byte region[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating that increasing the configured maximum nesting did not [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchange the underlying local buffer allocation or prevent the overflow.[0m              [2m                [0m
