[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The definition and allocation of the local array `nesting` in `json.c` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m131[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Its fixed size should align with the maximum allowed nesting constants. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code paths in `mg_json_get` that push into `nesting` when traversing JSON [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstructures [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m][0m[39m`, `[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. Ensure that every increment of `depth` or index [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minto `nesting` is guarded by the same limit checks and that the buffer itself is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msized appropriately.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interaction between `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` and any hardcoded assumptions [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mabout the maximum depth or buffer size statically allocated in `json.c`.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any use of `nesting` or related arrays beyond this function [0m[1;39m([0m[39mfor example, in [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrecursive calls or other JSON utilities[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that might rely on a matching maximum [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdepth.[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Core Analysis and Root Cause  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The stack-buffer-overflow in `mg_json_get` stems from a mismatch between the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize of the local array  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```c[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhere `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` defaults to [0m[1;36m30[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and the depth checks, which compare[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39magainst  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```c[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING  [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m default [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor raised to [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m in the last patch[0m[1;39m)[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       ```  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Because `depth` can legally grow to [0m[1;36m59[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mor [0m[1;36m127[0m[39m after the last patch[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m before [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe guard rejects further nesting,  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     the write `nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;` overruns the [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐byte buffer when `depth >= [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m30[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Strategy to Fix  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Unify the buffer size and the depth‐limit guard under a single macro, [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, and eliminate the old two‐macro mismatch.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Ensure that the local buffer is allocated with the same limit that the guard [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39menforces.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Tighten the guard to `depth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` so that any attempt to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpush at `depth == MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` before touching [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Steps [0m[1;39m([0m[39mto apply to the *initial* codebase[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. In `src/json.h`  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Remove the separate `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` and its default of [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Remove the old default `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` of [0m[1;36m60[0m[39m.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Introduce a single default for `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, e.g. [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m, if not [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39malready provided.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Define `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` as an alias to `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` for backward[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcompatibility [0m[1;39m([0m[39mso existing users of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` still compile[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/src/json.h[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/src/json.h[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #pragma once[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #include [0m[32m"arch.h"[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      #include [0m[32m"str.h"[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH [0m[1;36m30[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m60[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -#endif[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Unify maximum JSON nesting/depth under a single limit:[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +#ifndef MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +#define MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m compile‐time adjustable[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     #endif[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +[0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Alias for backward compatibility:[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +#define MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Error return values - negative. Successful returns are >= [0m[1;36m0[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      enum [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, MG_JSON_INVALID = [0m[1;36m-2[0m[39m, MG_JSON_NOT_FOUND = [0m[1;36m-3[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m;[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. In `src/json.c`  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Change the local buffer to use `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe single unified [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmacro[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m instead of `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH`.  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     - Ensure all depth checks use `>= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING` before modifying the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.  [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```diff[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     --- a/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +++ b/src/json.c[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Around line [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m:[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -  unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +  unsigned char nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mMG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       int i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, j = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, depth = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, ed = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, pos = [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, ci = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m, ei = [0m[1;36m-1[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      case S_VALUE:[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth == ed[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m j = i;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m{[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mc == [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     -      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth > MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     +      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdepth >= MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m return MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          break;[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - By collapsing both “depth” and “buffer size” into `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, there[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mis no longer a window in which `depth` can exceed the buffer’s capacity.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The tightened check [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`>=`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m guarantees that as soon as `depth` reaches the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconfigured maximum, the function returns `MG_JSON_TOO_DEEP` and never performs [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`nesting[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdepth++[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = c;`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack‐usage increase is minimal [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g. from [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m128[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, well within [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtypical limits, and is acceptable for preventing a security‐critical overflow.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Legacy code referring to `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` still works [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia the alias[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, so [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthere is no breaking change for existing builds that override one or the other [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmacro.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Preservation of Functionality and Tests  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All existing parsing logic and fuzzing harnesses remain unchanged, aside from [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe unified macro.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No external library, test, or harness code is modified.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch directly addresses the root‐cause buffer/guard mismatch and will [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39meliminate the ASan‐observed overflow.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential Side Effects and Mitigations  [0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Slightly larger stack allocation for the `nesting` array. Mitigation: the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincrease is modest [0m[1;39m([0m[39m< [0m[1;36m200[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If some code previously overrode only `MG_JSON_MAX_DEPTH` but not [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`, they must now override `MG_JSON_MAX_NESTING`. This is [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdocumented in the header comment.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzers and tests that relied on the old [0m[1;36m30[0m[39m‐level limit may now see earlier [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m“too deep” errors only after hitting the new limit; this is expected.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                   [0m[2;36m [0m[34mINFO    [0m Deleted work directory:                                                              ]8;id=280599;file:///home/qqor/crete/scripts/benchmark/__main__.py\[2m__main__.py[0m]8;;\[2m:[0m]8;id=432759;file:///home/qqor/crete/scripts/benchmark/__main__.py#314\[2m314[0m]8;;\

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mmongoose[0m               [2m               [0m
